|CKODESCRIPTION
|WKO===========

|YKOThe pnote command allows you to read your personal notebook.  All
adventurers carry scrolls, on which they may store important
information.

|CKBpnote a- <text>
|YKOThis will add the note <text> to your personal scroll.  The new
note will appear at the end of the scroll.

|CKBpnote d- <number of message>
|YKOThis will delete a message from the information scroll.  Any
message 'beneath' the deleted message will be bumped up one
number.  (If you have 3 messages and delete number 2, then
number 3 will become the new number 2.)

|WKBSyntax: |YKBpnote
